About
This Roman-themed shopping area features more than 160 upscale shops, including Fendi, Gucci, Dior, Versace, Chanel, and Cartier, plus art galleries and renowned restaurants like Spago and the Palm. Forum Shops at Caesars Palace by L-WIRE INTERNATIONAL

  • Sheila
    62 contributions
    Spectacular Shopping Experience at the Forum Shops at Caesars Palace
    The Forum Shops at Caesars Palace in Las Vegas offer an unparalleled shopping experience, combining luxury retail with a unique ambiance. One of the most captivating features is the ceiling, designed to resemble the sky and capable of changing colors to mimic the time of day. This stunning visual effect creates an immersive environment that makes you feel as though you are strolling through ancient Rome. With over 160 stores, including high-end brands like Gucci, Versace, and Louis Vuitton, the Forum Shops cater to those seeking luxury and quality. The mall's elegant decor, complete with statues, fountains, and even animatronic shows, adds to the opulent atmosphere. The combination of exquisite shopping options and breathtaking surroundings makes a visit to the Forum Shops a must when in Las Vegas. Despite often being crowded, the experience is well worth it. Whether you're there to shop or simply to admire the architecture and ambiance, the Forum Shops at Caesars Palace provide a memorable escape from the hustle and bustle of the Strip.
    Visited October 2023
    Traveled with friends

Oct 2023 Friends
The Forum Shops at Caesars Palace in Las Vegas offer an unparalleled shopping experience, combining luxury retail with a unique ambiance. One of the most captivating features is the ceiling, designed to resemble the sky and capable of changing colors to mimic the time of day. This stunning visual effect creates an immersive environment that makes you feel as though you are strolling through ancient Rome.

With over 160 stores, including high-end brands like Gucci, Versace, and Louis Vuitton, the Forum Shops cater to those seeking luxury and quality. The mall's elegant decor, complete with statues, fountains, and even animatronic shows, adds to the opulent atmosphere. The combination of exquisite shopping options and breathtaking surroundings makes a visit to the Forum Shops a must when in Las Vegas.

Despite often being crowded, the experience is well worth it. Whether you're there to shop or simply to admire the architecture and ambiance, the Forum Shops at Caesars Palace provide a memorable escape from the hustle and bustle of the Strip.
